CONSENT/PII
-------------------------------------------------------
The dataset from the Philippine-Traffic-Sign-Dataset computer vision model consists 
of public traffic sign images that are captured in open space/public roads. Due to these, 
the data that were collected are representing the public infrastructure. without any private 
individuals/humans as a subject. 

The dataset complies with the Philippine Data Privacy Act of 2012. The dataset have been 
reviewed to ensure that no Personally Identifiable Information (PII) is exposed. 
All of the data used have blurred faces and vehicle plate numbers. 
to ensure that the Data Privacy Act is being conducted. 

REPRESENTATIVENESS: JUSTIFICATION
-------------------------------------------------------
The dataset was chosen because it represent the real world driving conditions. 
The image were captured in different time of the day which provides the needed 
natural lighting and different angles.

